<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Khloe Kardashian successfully surprised her sister Kourtney on her 41st birthday with an epic car parade in front of her front yard. </p>

<p>Kourtney's birthday occurred on April 18, not long after large gatherings were banned and social distancing came into effect in response to the coronavirus pandemic.   </p>

<p>But Khloe, 36, was still determined to safely gather the family together and make the birthday an unforgettable one for her big sister. </p>

<p>Birthday surprise! Khloe Kardashian successfully surprised her sister Kourtney on her 41st birthday with an epic car parade in front of her front yard</p>

<p>Turning lemons into lemonade: Kourtney's birthday occurred not long after large gatherings were banned and social distancing came into effect in response to the coronavirus pandemic </p>

<p>In a new KUWTK teaser, Khloe can be seen organizing the big event just minutes before leading a giant procession of cars through Kourtney's neighborhood.</p>

<p>'So it's Kourtney's birthday, and we are going to drive by Kourtney's house, blasting birthday music, honking horns, annoying all the neighbors, and everyone did such a great job decorating their cars,' Khloe explained in a confessional. </p>

<p>Khloe secretly teamed up with Kourtney's daughter Penelope, eight, to make her vision happen.</p>

<p>Before driving by her house, Khloe called her niece to fill her in on the plan.</p>

<p>Hatching a plan: Khloe unveils her surprise plans to her niece Penelope </p>

<p>Her little one: Meanwhile, Khloe and Tristan's daughter True scampered about the front yard</p>

<p>Everyone's in: Kendall Jenner and Kim Kardashian joined in on the surprise </p>

<p>Hoppy birthday: Khloe put on a rabbit mask as she prepared to lead the car parade</p>

<p>Start your engines! Friends and family celebrated Kourtney's birthday from the safety of their cars</p>

<p>'Hey Penelope can your mom hear me?' Khloe says on the phone.</p>

<p>'No,' Penlope replies.</p>

<p>'Okay good because we have a surprise. I'm gonna need you to do something for me. I need your help with getting your mommy out the front door and I'm gonna have a surprise for her on the street. </p>

<p>'But I can't tell her, you're just gonna have to say, "Mom, can you come outside? I need to show you something." But don't ruin the surprise! You can take all the credit!'</p>

<p>Make some noise! Participants honked their horns and blasted music in front of Kourtney's house</p>

<p>Family fun: Kim's children North and Saint showed their support from the moon roof </p>

<p>Here comes the party! Khloe clutched a festive display of baby pink balloons </p>

<p>'Okay,' Penelope replies.</p>

<p>'You got it, P!' Tristan says encouragingly to the youngster.</p>

<p>Next, Khloe led the giant procession of cars from atop her own vehicle.  </p>

<p>'Everybody line up and get ready for the car parade!' Khloe says through her blow horn. </p>

<p>Here comes the birthday girl: Kourtney made her way outside of the house with her daughter following close behind </p>

<p>Let's do this! A car drove by wielding a 'Happy BDay Kourt' sign </p>

<p>The festively-decorated cars drive by Kourtney's house, where they honk their horns and blast music. </p>

<p>Kourtney steps outside of her car, beaming with delight while recording the whole thing on her phone.</p>

<p>'Best birthday ever!' Khloe declares.</p>

<p>After the parade was over, Kourtney waved good bye to everyone.</p>

<p>'Bye love you guys!' she shouts.</p>

<p>Season 18 of Keeping Up With The Kardashians will return to E! on September 17 at 8pm, and will document the family reacting to the pandemic. </p>

<p>Let the good times roll: A giant procession of cars crowded together down the street </p>

